	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />One thing that is concerning is that I do only see one latch, not two; with only one latch clock input there can't be two disjoint registers.<br /><br />To decode the memory region from $6000-$7FFF requires <a href="https://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/PRG_RAM_circuit" class="postlink">hardware</a> that isn't present â€” there's only a 74'32, a 74'161, and that KC5373 appears to be a charge pump ( = CIC stunner).<br /><br />Given the values that are written, the functionality should be <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">Mask: $8000 ; $8000 - [.... PPCC] ; bus conflicts</tt>.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


